What is local search?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Local search is a metaheuristic method to optimize solutions for NP-hard
 problems.
 Local search algorithms compares a certain solution with surrounding solutions.
 Each surrounding solution are evaluated and the best one is chosen.
 This repeats itself many times, until the optimized solution is found.
 But how does this algorithm knows if the best solution is found and how
 does it get there?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The algorithm obverses different states (possible solutions).
 Each state is evaluated based on a chosen heuristic.
 In the following example we use just one heuristic, so it can be drawn
 on paper.
 In the real world multiple dimensions are needed.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Because there is no end to this algorithm, local search is a approximation
 or incomplete algorithm.
